"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 27, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104umx1665702765900.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/umx1665702765900.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/umx1665702765900.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"umx1665702765900\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n           \n Debugging in a Web Environment\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"umx1665702765900__debugging_in_a_web_environment_78539\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Debugging in a web environment requires special techniques because there is no Uniface client application to debug. For each HTTP request, Uniface starts an instance of the requested server page, and terminates it after the request is handled.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"umx1665702765900__p_d22724e1_d22725e1_d22726e1\">You can use remote debugging to connect the Uniface Debugger with a Uniface Web Server over TCP or TLS. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"syc1665702765825.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/syc1665702765825.html\" title=\"Debugging a web application requires the use of remote debugging, in which the Uniface Debugger and the Uniface Web Application Server communicate with each other over a network. They can be running on the same machine or on different machines, and the network protocol can be TCP or TLS. Either one can be started first, but their configurations must match.\">Debugging a Web Application</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"umx1665702765900__p_d22727e1_d22728e1_d22729e1\">You can also change some configuration settings for debugging purposes:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"umx1665702765900__li_d11120e1_d11121e1_d11122e1\">If you only need a ProcScript trace, use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$PROC_TRACING</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$PUTMESS_LOG_FILE</span> in the assignment file of the application server. You can view the tracing result from the log file or in the browser. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fvy1665702765976.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fvy1665702765976.html\" title=\"To get the ProcScript trace information, you can use $PROC_TRACING and $PUTMESS_LOG_FILE in the assignment file of the Uniface Server. You can view the tracing result from the log file or in the browser.\">Using ProcScript Tracing in a Web Application</a>.\n            </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"umx1665702765900__li_d11123e1_d11124e1_d11125e1\">When debugging dynamic server pages, it can be helpful to set the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$JSON_INDENT</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$JSON_SHOWNAMES</span> assignment settings to make the pages more human-readable.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"umx1665702765900__p_d22730e1_d22731e1_d22732e1\">Browsers also have developer tools that can be used to monitor and debug JavaScript code execution. These are available from the browser's menu. For example:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"umx1665702765900__li_d11126e1_d11127e1_d11128e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://developers.google.com/web%2Ftools%2Fchrome-devtools%2F%3Fhl%3Den\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Chrome Dev Tools</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"umx1665702765900__li_d11129e1_d11130e1_d11131e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Tools\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Firefox Developer Tools</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"umx1665702765900__li_d11132e1_d11133e1_d11134e1\"><a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://developer.apple.com/safari/tools/\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Safari Web\n               Development Tools</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"umx1665702765900__section_qjz_jq1_4cc\">\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://learn.rocketsoftware.com/course/view.php?id=481\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Learn More\" class=\"image\" id=\"umx1665702765900__image_m2z_144_vdc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/My_Learn_More_Button.jpg?_LANG=enus\"/></a></p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/phs1665702879738.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Configuring the Web Test Environment</a><p>Uniface provides a default web environment that allows you to test your web applications. This is automatically configured during installation.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qhw1665702765447.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Debugger</a><p>The Uniface Debugger is a Uniface application that can connect to a local or remote Uniface application process so that you can conduct step-by-step, real time analysis of the executing ProcScript. It enables you to find and correct ProcScript errors, investigate application behavior, and improve code in all types of Uniface application.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/egv1665702669743.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Web Application Error Pages</a><p>An error is displayed when a problem occurs in executing the desired Uniface service, for example, if an incorrect URL is provided.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532756\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532756\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Debugging in a Web Environment Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 27, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Debugging in a Web Environment Debugging in a web environment requires special techniques because there is no Uniface client application to debug. For each HTTP request, Uniface starts an instance of the requested server page, and terminates it after the request is handled. You can use remote debugging to connect the Uniface Debugger with a Uniface Web Server over TCP or TLS. For more information, see Debugging a Web Application . You can also change some configuration settings for debugging purposes: If you only need a ProcScript trace, use $PROC_TRACING and $PUTMESS_LOG_FILE in the assignment file of the application server. You can view the tracing result from the log file or in the browser. For more information, see Using ProcScript Tracing in a Web Application . When debugging dynamic server pages, it can be helpful to set the $JSON_INDENT and $JSON_SHOWNAMES assignment settings to make the pages more human-readable. Browsers also have developer tools that can be used to monitor and debug JavaScript code execution. These are available from the browser's menu. For example: Chrome Dev Tools Firefox Developer Tools Safari Web Development Tools Related Links Configuring the Web Test Environment Uniface provides a default web environment that allows you to test your web applications. This is automatically configured during installation. Uniface Debugger The Uniface Debugger is a Uniface application that can connect to a local or remote Uniface application process so that you can conduct step-by-step, real time analysis of the executing ProcScript. It enables you to find and correct ProcScript errors, investigate application behavior, and improve code in all types of Uniface application. Web Application Error Pages An error is displayed when a problem occurs in executing the desired Uniface service, for example, if an incorrect URL is provided. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}